<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="279" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,495,1868,1927]" box="[151,495,1868,1894]" pageId="8" pageNumber="279">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,495,1868,1894]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="8" pageNumber="279" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,495,1868,1894]" pageId="8" pageNumber="279">
<taxonomicName box="[151,394,1868,1894]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Mahellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="279" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ungulatus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,394,1868,1894]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="279">Mahellus ungulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[402,495,1868,1894]" pageId="8" pageNumber="279" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,495,1868,1927]" box="[151,409,1902,1927]" pageId="8" pageNumber="279">Figs 89, 17, 40–47, 52.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="280" pageId="8" pageNumber="279" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,1974,2035]" pageId="8" pageNumber="279">Ochraceous brown, mesonotum and scutellum with few dark brown spots, forewing veins brownish with ochraceous spots. Apices of hind femora, hind tarsi, bases of setae on hind tibiae, brown and claws dark brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,151,789]" pageId="9" pageNumber="280">
Male pygofer in lateral view more or less triangular, broad anteriorly and narrowed posteriorly with sclerotized process along dorsal margin, curved mesally and acuminate (
<figureCitation box="[868,959,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 40 – 47" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[213,1386,201,1926]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[179,1408,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 40 – 47. Mahellus ungulatus sp. nov., male genitalia. 40. Pygofer, lateral view; 41. Pygofer caudoventral process, lateral view; 42. Connective, dorsal view; 43. Style, dorsal view; 44. Subgenital plate, ventral view; 45. Aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; 46. Aedeagus and dorsal connective, dorsal view; 47. Apex of aedeagal shaft, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/569770/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="280">Figs 40</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[975,1007,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 48 – 52" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1716,1739]" captionTargetBox="[168,1421,432,1697]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,419,1713]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 48 – 52. Speceis of Mahellus. 48. Chaetotaxy of forefemur of M. distanti; 49. Chaetotaxy of metabasitarsus and second tarsomete of M. distanti, ventral view; 50 – 52. Posterior portion of male pygofer of Mahellus, dorsal view showing dorsal marginal sclerotized process: 50. M. cardoni sp. nov.; 51. M. distanti; 52. M. ungulatus sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/569771/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="280">52</figureCitation>
); with ventral blade-like process not exceeding apex of pygofer, broadened distally with 5–7 teeth-like projections (
<figureCitation box="[1048,1125,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 40 – 47" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[213,1386,201,1926]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[179,1408,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 40 – 47. Mahellus ungulatus sp. nov., male genitalia. 40. Pygofer, lateral view; 41. Pygofer caudoventral process, lateral view; 42. Connective, dorsal view; 43. Style, dorsal view; 44. Subgenital plate, ventral view; 45. Aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; 46. Aedeagus and dorsal connective, dorsal view; 47. Apex of aedeagal shaft, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/569770/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="280">Fig.41</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate long and narrow with posterior spine-like projection; ventral surface with a few hair-like setae, posterior area with row of short stout setae (
<figureCitation box="[352,438,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURES 40 – 47" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[213,1386,201,1926]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[179,1408,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 40 – 47. Mahellus ungulatus sp. nov., male genitalia. 40. Pygofer, lateral view; 41. Pygofer caudoventral process, lateral view; 42. Connective, dorsal view; 43. Style, dorsal view; 44. Subgenital plate, ventral view; 45. Aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; 46. Aedeagus and dorsal connective, dorsal view; 47. Apex of aedeagal shaft, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/569770/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="280">Fig. 44</figureCitation>
). Connective Y-shaped with median longitudinal apodeme, stem short (
<figureCitation box="[1254,1340,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURES 40 – 47" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[213,1386,201,1926]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[179,1408,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 40 – 47. Mahellus ungulatus sp. nov., male genitalia. 40. Pygofer, lateral view; 41. Pygofer caudoventral process, lateral view; 42. Connective, dorsal view; 43. Style, dorsal view; 44. Subgenital plate, ventral view; 45. Aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; 46. Aedeagus and dorsal connective, dorsal view; 47. Apex of aedeagal shaft, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/569770/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="280">Fig. 42</figureCitation>
). Dorsal connective membranous, unpigmented band-like. Style uniformly broad basally, tapered apically (
<figureCitation box="[1331,1424,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 40 – 47" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[213,1386,201,1926]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[179,1408,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 40 – 47. Mahellus ungulatus sp. nov., male genitalia. 40. Pygofer, lateral view; 41. Pygofer caudoventral process, lateral view; 42. Connective, dorsal view; 43. Style, dorsal view; 44. Subgenital plate, ventral view; 45. Aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; 46. Aedeagus and dorsal connective, dorsal view; 47. Apex of aedeagal shaft, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/569770/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="280">Fig. 43</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus asymmetrical, long and slender compared to that of 
<taxonomicName box="[853,974,368,392]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Mahellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="280" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="distanti">
<emphasis box="[853,974,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="280">M. distanti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, in lateral aspect broad in basal half then narrowed and of uniform width to apex, with pair of subapical processes serrated distally, apical process arising on dorsal margin, other subapically on lateral margin, gonopore large on dorsal surface of shaft almost at midlength (
<figureCitation box="[159,290,476,501]" captionStart="FIGURES 40 – 47" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[213,1386,201,1926]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[179,1408,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 40 – 47. Mahellus ungulatus sp. nov., male genitalia. 40. Pygofer, lateral view; 41. Pygofer caudoventral process, lateral view; 42. Connective, dorsal view; 43. Style, dorsal view; 44. Subgenital plate, ventral view; 45. Aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; 46. Aedeagus and dorsal connective, dorsal view; 47. Apex of aedeagal shaft, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/569770/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="280">Figs 45–47</figureCitation>
). Segment X in lateral aspect longer than broad, with flat ventral surface, in dorsal aspect broad at base and slightly narrowed distally, without ventral process.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,151,789]" pageId="9" pageNumber="280">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,381,548,573]" pageId="9" pageNumber="280">Measurements.</emphasis>
Male 7.0 mm long, 1.9 mm wide across eyes and 2.1 mm wide across posterolateral angles of pronotum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
